  <description type="morphology">Shrubs to 10+ dm. Leaves petiolate; petiole 3–15 mm; blade 1-veined from base, narrowly elliptic, obovate, or ovate, (10–)25–50(–75) × (5–)8–30 mm, &lt;margins ± undulate, not revolute&gt;. Inflorescences solitary flowers or cymes. Flowers: sepals 5, &lt;apices acuminate&gt;; petals pink, purple, or reddish, sometimes yellowish near bases, 20–30 mm; styles 1–3+ mm; &lt;stigmas borne at level of anthers&gt;. Capsules 5-locular. 2n = 18 (Europe).</description>
